sections.comments: CPSC 110 is the shortest route to CPSC 210 and the rest of the Computer Science major.  If you plan to complete a Computer Science major or honours degree (including combined majors and dual majors) or need CPSC 110 to fulfill a degree requirement you should take CPSC 110. Students who are not planning to focus on Computer Science may also find that CPSC 110 best matches their needs and interests.  For more information on how to select a first year CS course go to: https://www.cs.ubc.ca/students/undergrad/courses/choose-your-first-courseWhen this course fills additional labs will be added, however, you may be required to adjust your timetable to fit a lab into your schedule.
